-- Kazzinc, Verny to Buy Kazakh Gold Producer for 30 Billion Tenge
-- B y   N a r i m a n   G i z i t d i n o v
-- 2013-02-19T09:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-19/kazzinc-verny-to-buy-kazakh-gold-producer-for-30-billion-tenge.html
Verny Capital , a Kazakh investment
management group part-owned by billionaire  Bulat Utemuratov , and
Kazzinc are spending about 30 billion tenge ($199 million) to
buy a Kazakh gold producer.  Kazzinc acquired 89.5 percent of TOO Orion Minerals from
Cammex, with Verny Capital obtaining the rest of the company,
the Astana-based investment vehicle said in a statement
distributed today in the Kazakh capital, Astana.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nariman Gizitdinov in Almaty at 
 ngizitdinov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
